UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1386418100000082
KW  - Trading arrangements
KW  - Market microstructure
KW  - Foreign exchange
AB  - It is common in the literature to assume that trading arrangements are exogenous. Yet, the sheer variety of existing arrangements suggests that they are in fact subject to choice. This paper formally endogenizes the choice of a trading arrangement. I argue that if the design of an arrangement affects trading outcomes, then rational, strategically-acting agents will opt for the arrangement that facilitates trading and leads to price discovery. I demonstrate the general argument in the context of emerging foreign exchange markets which exhibit a particularly wide variety of trading arrangements.
